      "timestep_posted": 45
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_17_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_17",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This powerplant utilizes individual throttle bodies and Double VANOS variable valve timing to produce a linear power band peaking at its 8,000 RPM redline. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise 6-speed manual transmission and a factory M-Variable limited-slip differential. This example has undergone critical preventative maintenance, including rear subframe reinforcement and a comprehensive cooling system overhaul. The suspension geometry remains tight, providing the telepathic turn-in these chassis are known for. While the exterior shows minor road wear consistent with driver-focused use, the mechanical vitals are robust, making this an ideal candidate for the purist seeking a visceral, naturally aspirated driving experience.",
